  "id": "019d37a8-eb2b-77d2-a276-438d9ce0530c",
  "content": "# Agent Teams Phase 3: Graph Edges and Identity Correlation -- Decision Record (2026-03-29)\n## What: Implemented 6 graph edge types and subagent-to-teammate identity correlation for the agent-teams adapter.\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. EdgeHint protocol extension: Added edge_hints field to D75 SourceMetadata rather than a separate edge response type. This keeps the adapter as a pure data emitter and the kernel as the edge creation engine. Backward compatible via serde(default, skip_serializing_if).\n2. Three-tier edge resolution: Same-batch HashMap lookup, cross-batch store.get_by_source_version(), deferred to .pending-edges file. This eliminates adapter ordering dependency between session history and agent-teams runs.\n3. Description-based correlation as primary signal: Matching Agent tool call descriptions to teammate-message summary tags is structural (same string) and does not depend on user content or timing. Temporal fallback uses date-aware epoch seconds within 30-second window.\n4. Atomic file writes for .pending-edges: Uses temp-then-rename pattern to prevent corruption from concurrent ingest runs.\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- timestamp_diff_ms must include the date component to handle midnight crossings correctly in temporal correlation\n- unsigned_abs() as i64 can silently overflow; use i64::try_from for defensive coding\n- The discusses edge heuristic only fires when messages have explicit task_assignment fields; messages discussing tasks without that field produce no edge\n## What Blocked / Surprised:\n- The adapter binary's local SourceMetadata struct must mirror the kernel's canonical EdgeHint exactly since they communicate via JSONL, not shared Rust types",
